ning of modern German <i>Vetter</i> is ‘cousin’. Compare   Vedder  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vedder","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Wolf, Hellmuth, Kurt, Orlo, Dietrich, Eckhard, Helmut.","German and Dutch: relationship name from Middle Low German and Middle Dutch <i>vedder</i> ‘(paternal) uncle, cousin’, which was also used more generally to denote any male relative. Compare   Vetter  .","History: Many of the American Vedders are descended from Harmen Albertse Vedder from the Netherlands, who was in Beverwyck in New Netherland (now Albany, NY) before 1657 and died in Schenectady, NY, in or before 1715."]},{"name":"Vetters","meanings":["German: from the possessive form of   Vetter  ."]}]},{"name":"Conrad","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual English spelling of <i>Konrad</i>, a Germanic personal name derived from <i>kuon</i> ‘bold’ + <i>rad</i> ‘counsel’. It was used occasionally in Britain in the Middle Ages in honour of a 10th-century bishop of Constance, but modern use in the English-speaking world is a reimportation from Germany dating mainly from the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Conrad Vetter was born in 1562, in Oberamt Geislingen, Württemberg, Germany as the son of Hans Vetter. He married Barbara Panthaleon on 18 March 1585, in Oberamt Geislingen, Württemberg, Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 3 daughters."},"et":{"1562–":"1562–Surnud","1550–Female":"1550–Surnud","1562–Male":"1562–Surnud","1560–Female":"1560–Surnud","1586–Female":"1586–Surnud","1587–Male":"1587–Surnud","1589–Male":"1589–Surnud","1591–Female":"1591–Surnud","1592–Female":"1592–Surnud","1515–Male":"1515–Surnud","18 Mar 1585":"18. märts 1585","25 March 1586":"25. märts 1586","1550":"1550","1560":"1560","1592":"1592","29 Jun 1587":"29. juuni 1587","1591":"1591","4 Aug 1592":"4. august 1592","1589":"1589","1587":"1587","24 Jun 1591":"24. juuni 1591